# Project Standards

## Button Standards

### Types

1. Main Action Buttons:

   - Medium size, text only
   - Example: `<Button variant="add">Add New</Button>`
   - Use for primary page actions

2. Form Buttons:

   - Medium size, text only
   - Save before Cancel
   - Example:
     ```jsx
     <div className="d-flex gap-2">
       <Button variant="save">Save</Button>
       <Button variant="cancel">Cancel</Button>
     </div>
     ```

3. Table Action Buttons:

   - Small size, icon only
   - Edit before Delete
   - Example:
     ```jsx
     <div className="d-flex justify-content-center gap-2">
       <Button variant="edit" iconOnly size="sm" />
       <Button variant="delete" iconOnly size="sm" />
     </div>
     ```

4. Dropdown:

   - use the Dropdown components found in Frontend/src/Components/UI/Dropdown.jsx

5. Filters:

   - use the Filter components found in Frontend/src/Components/Logic/

6. Routes:
   - use the Routes components found in Server/Routes/

### Variants

- add/save: green, for creation/saving actions
- edit/view: blue, for modification/viewing actions
- delete: red, for deletion actions
- cancel/print: gray, for cancellation/utility actions

### Sizes

- md: default, for main actions and form buttons
- sm: for table actions and secondary buttons

### Layout

- Use gap-2 for button spacing
- Center align table action buttons
- Main action buttons at top of content area
- Form buttons at bottom of forms

// End Button Standards

